data.text:
Shawn Corey Carter (born: December 4, 1969 (1969-12-04) [age 54]), better known professionally as JAY-Z, is an American musician, singer, and songwriter, who performs the genres of rap, hip hop, and pop.

Albums[]

Since he became active in 1988 he's released a total of thirteen studio albums, including

Reasonable Doubt (1996)

In My Lifetime, Vol. 1 (1997)

Vol. 2...Hard Knock Life (1998)

Vol. 3... Life and Times of S. Carter (1999)

The Dynasty: Roc La Familia (2000)

The Blueprint (2001)

The Blueprint 2: The Gift & The Curse, (2002),

The Black Album (2003)

Kingdom Come (2006)

American Gangster (2007)

The Blueprint 3 (2009)

Magna Carta... Holy Grail (2013)

4:44 (2017)

five collaboration albums, which included

The Best of Both Worlds (2002)

Unfinished Business (2004)

Collision Course, (2004 with Linkin Park)

Watch the Throne (2011 with Kanye West)

Everything Is Love (2018 with Beyonc√©)

two live albums, which includes

Jay-Z: Unplugged (2002)

Live in Brooklyn (2012)

five compilation albums which includes

Chapter One: Greatest Hits, (2002)

Blueprints 2.1, (2003)

Bring It On: The Best of Jay-Z (2003)

Greatest Hits (2006)

Jay-Z: The Hits Collection Volume One (2010)

one soundtrack album which includes

Streets Is Watching, (1998)

one mixtape which includes

S. Carter Collection (2003)
